The experiment `bow_20260514_145515_run_01` using a Bag of Words (BoW) architecture achieved a reasonable performance with an F1 score of 0.7161 and accuracy of 0.78. The use of TF-IDF vectorization and a logistic regression model with a regularization parameter `C=0.5` seems to have contributed positively to the results. However, the experiment could potentially benefit from tuning additional hyperparameters such as the maximum number of features (`max_features`) or exploring different n-gram ranges (`ngram_max`). For the next run, consider experimenting with a larger vocabulary size and possibly incorporating character-level n-grams to capture more nuanced patterns in the text data. Additionally, evaluating the impact of varying the `min_df` threshold could help in optimizing feature selection.